I was doing a conference
in the DC area,

00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:05.830 align:middle line:90%
and I made the statement.

00:18:05.830 --> 00:18:09.860 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I would love
to get my hands on some DNA

00:18:09.860 --> 00:18:12.620 align:middle line:84%
from life that's
not from this world.

00:18:12.620 --> 00:18:14.900 align:middle line:84%
And if it's carbon-based
life, and if the message is

00:18:14.900 --> 00:18:15.210 align:middle line:90%
the same--

00:18:15.210 --> 00:18:15.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The same.

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.750 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: --then we know
that we have a common--

00:18:17.750 --> 00:18:18.708 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A common goal.

00:18:18.708 --> 00:18:19.800 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: --a common goal.

00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:20.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Wouldn't
that be exciting?

00:18:20.970 --> 00:18:22.460 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: Well, there's a man
that came forward and said,

00:18:22.460 --> 00:18:24.335 align:middle line:84%
when you're ready for
that DNA, let me know.

00:18:24.335 --> 00:18:25.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's got it?

00:18:25.210 --> 00:18:25.970 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: I don't know.

00:18:25.970 --> 00:18:28.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Maybe from some
Martian meteorite, right?

00:18:28.070 --> 00:18:28.830 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: I don't know.

00:18:28.830 --> 00:18:29.830 align:middle line:90%
You know, we don't know.

00:18:29.830 --> 00:18:30.890 align:middle line:90%
We don't know.

00:18:30.890 --> 00:18:32.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You going
to take him up on it?

00:18:32.760 --> 00:18:34.430 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I'm going to call
him from your cellphone number,

00:18:34.430 --> 00:18:35.510 align:middle line:84%
George, not from my
cell phone number.

00:18:35.510 --> 00:18:36.176 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Thanks.

00:18:36.176 --> 00:18:38.320 align:middle line:90%
Block your number.

00:18:38.320 --> 00:18:40.740 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I'm not
ready for that yet.

00:18:40.740 --> 00:18:43.910 align:middle line:84%
When we were developing
the algorithms--

00:18:43.910 --> 00:18:45.770 align:middle line:84%
and there are very
complex algorithms now

00:18:45.770 --> 00:18:49.500 align:middle line:84%
to help look at the
DNA in new ways.

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:50.380 align:middle line:90%
So here we are.

00:18:50.380 --> 00:18:51.740 align:middle line:90%
We come full circle.

00:18:51.740 --> 00:18:55.570 align:middle line:84%
We are at this crisis
point in civilization

00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:59.024 align:middle line:84%
when we're facing more crises
of such great magnitude.

00:18:59.024 --> 00:19:00.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Than ever before
that I can remember.

00:19:00.940 --> 00:19:03.870 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: --based on our
division, on our separation.

00:19:03.870 --> 00:19:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And if there is some way
that we could bring forward

00:19:08.430 --> 00:19:12.190 align:middle line:84%
in a really powerful
meaningful way something that

00:19:12.190 --> 00:19:17.460 align:middle line:84%
casts an entire new
light on us as a family

00:19:17.460 --> 00:19:19.590 align:middle line:84%
and what that family
means, I think

00:19:19.590 --> 00:19:22.870 align:middle line:84%
it would give us a reason to
look at things differently.

00:19:22.870 --> 00:19:24.412 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean it
would force us to.

00:19:24.412 --> 00:19:25.036 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:19:25.036 --> 00:19:27.440 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: It means it would
give us a scientific reason

00:19:27.440 --> 00:19:30.410 align:middle line:84%
to look at one another and think
of ourselves very differently.

00:19:30.410 --> 00:19:33.360 align:middle line:84%
I know for myself,
once I found this code,

00:19:33.360 --> 00:19:36.930 align:middle line:84%
I felt differently about myself
knowing that within every cell

00:19:36.930 --> 00:19:42.760 align:middle line:84%
of my body, God eternal-- it's
Y-H-V-G, the Hebrew letters.

00:19:42.760 --> 00:19:47.630 align:middle line:84%
Y-H, yah, is actually one of
the forms of the name of God

00:19:47.630 --> 00:19:50.480 align:middle line:84%
that we find in the Torah that
was removed over 6,800 times.

00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:56.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did it baffle you
as to who put the code there?

00:19:56.570 --> 00:20:00.850 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I've sensed that
there's an intentionality.

00:20:00.850 --> 00:20:02.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: From?

00:20:02.090 --> 00:20:03.160 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Regarding us.

00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:08.290 align:middle line:84%
And when we go to look, now,
at Darwin's idea of evolution,

00:20:08.290 --> 00:20:10.750 align:middle line:84%
2,000 years ago we
appeared on this Earth.

00:20:10.750 --> 00:20:12.170 align:middle line:84%
We don't know
where we came from.

00:20:12.170 --> 00:20:15.860 align:middle line:84%
And what made us different
from so many of the other forms

00:20:15.860 --> 00:20:18.330 align:middle line:84%
of life was human
chromosome number two,

00:20:18.330 --> 00:20:20.760 align:middle line:84%
the largest that had
been infused with two

00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:22.810 align:middle line:90%
telomere-to-telomere fusions.

00:20:22.810 --> 00:20:24.730 align:middle line:84%
Geneticists
acknowledged the fusion.

00:20:24.730 --> 00:20:27.062 align:middle line:84%
They say, we can't
say how it happened.

00:20:27.062 --> 00:20:28.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But they
know it happened.

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:31.910 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And it did not happen
under natural circumstances.

00:20:31.910 --> 00:20:33.970 align:middle line:84%
They said this would
not happen in nature.

00:20:33.970 --> 00:20:37.150 align:middle line:84%
Something has forced
this chromosome

00:20:37.150 --> 00:20:40.250 align:middle line:84%
or this telomere-to-telomere
fusion between these two

00:20:40.250 --> 00:20:41.530 align:middle line:90%
chromosomes.

00:20:41.530 --> 00:20:43.600 align:middle line:84%
So I think what we're
getting, George,

00:20:43.600 --> 00:20:46.970 align:middle line:84%
is we've had a sense,
so many people,

00:20:46.970 --> 00:20:49.010 align:middle line:84%
that there's much more
to us than evolution

00:20:49.010 --> 00:20:50.150 align:middle line:90%
has led us to believe.

00:20:50.150 --> 00:20:53.510 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean that
evolution didn't occur.

00:20:53.510 --> 00:20:56.590 align:middle line:84%
As a scientist I can
say it did to a point,

00:20:56.590 --> 00:20:58.990 align:middle line:84%
but there's a point where
evolution does not explain

00:20:58.990 --> 00:21:02.110 align:middle line:84%
our existence and cannot
account for what we find.

00:21:02.110 --> 00:21:05.560 align:middle line:84%
And I think this study,
this kind of work

00:21:05.560 --> 00:21:07.530 align:middle line:84%
where we're crossing the
traditional boundaries

00:21:07.530 --> 00:21:10.040 align:middle line:84%
between science
and spirituality--

00:21:10.040 --> 00:21:13.170 align:middle line:84%
a scholar studying the
text would never find this.

00:21:13.170 --> 00:21:14.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A scientist would?

00:21:14.430 --> 00:21:15.580 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: A scientist
looking at the elements

00:21:15.580 --> 00:21:17.580 align:middle line:84%
in the periodic
table or a geneticist

00:21:17.580 --> 00:21:20.327 align:middle line:84%
would never find it because
they're compartmentalized.

00:21:20.327 --> 00:21:21.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You need a combination.

00:21:21.660 --> 00:21:23.576 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: But the world
doesn't work that way.

00:21:23.576 --> 00:21:26.530 align:middle line:84%
So we are gifting
ourselves the ability

00:21:26.530 --> 00:21:28.850 align:middle line:84%
to see the world as it
is through what the world

00:21:28.850 --> 00:21:31.290 align:middle line:84%
a sharing with us if
we're open enough.

00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:33.160 align:middle line:90%
But the science has to be rigid.

00:21:33.160 --> 00:21:36.580 align:middle line:84%
It has to be based upon
what science is telling us.

00:21:36.580 --> 00:21:40.530 align:middle line:84%
So the periodic table
describes the elements that

00:21:40.530 --> 00:21:43.410 align:middle line:90%
make the DNA in our bodies.

00:21:43.410 --> 00:21:45.490 align:middle line:84%
There's a mathematic
link between that

00:21:45.490 --> 00:21:48.910 align:middle line:84%
and the letters of
the ancient alphabets.

00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:51.960 align:middle line:84%
How that link got there, who
put it there, I have no idea.

00:21:51.960 --> 00:21:55.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As I was flying
here, Greg, from Los Angeles

00:21:55.390 --> 00:21:57.790 align:middle line:84%
to Denver-- and I'm
looking around the plane.

00:21:57.790 --> 00:22:00.705 align:middle line:84%
And there's all these
people sitting on the plane.

00:22:00.705 --> 00:22:04.400 align:middle line:84%
And it just dawns on me-- and
I do this a lot-- every one

00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:05.830 align:middle line:90%
of them is an individual.

00:22:05.830 --> 00:22:08.900 align:middle line:84%
They've got their own little
situation, their problems,

00:22:08.900 --> 00:22:11.570 align:middle line:90%
their happiness, their families.

00:22:11.570 --> 00:22:13.540 align:middle line:90%
Every one of them.

00:22:13.540 --> 00:22:15.870 align:middle line:84%
But the question I
kept asking myself

00:22:15.870 --> 00:22:21.200 align:middle line:84%
as I looked at this entire
plane full of people, why?

00:22:21.200 --> 00:22:22.310 align:middle line:90%
What's the reason?

00:22:22.310 --> 00:22:24.050 align:middle line:90%
What are they here for?

00:22:24.050 --> 00:22:25.340 align:middle line:90%
Some had briefcases.

00:22:25.340 --> 00:22:27.060 align:middle line:90%
Some had purses.

00:22:27.060 --> 00:22:29.350 align:middle line:90%
Some had tablets.

00:22:29.350 --> 00:22:30.230 align:middle line:90%
Who are they?

00:22:30.230 --> 00:22:31.960 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:22:31.960 --> 00:22:34.450 align:middle line:90%
I still can't get that answer.

00:22:34.450 --> 00:22:36.130 align:middle line:84%
You, of course, have
brought up a series

00:22:36.130 --> 00:22:39.450 align:middle line:84%
of six questions in one
of our previous shows

00:22:39.450 --> 00:22:42.590 align:middle line:90%
that asks those questions too.

00:22:42.590 --> 00:22:44.800 align:middle line:84%
But will we ever
get that answer?

00:22:44.800 --> 00:22:48.120 align:middle line:90%
Why are we here?

00:22:48.120 --> 00:22:51.260 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I think we will
have the answer, George.

00:22:51.260 --> 00:22:54.220 align:middle line:84%
The question is, will
we be willing to accept

00:22:54.220 --> 00:22:55.610 align:middle line:90%
what the answer says to us.

00:22:55.610 --> 00:22:56.735 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is it frightening?

00:22:56.735 --> 00:22:58.500 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I don't
think it's frightening.

00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:01.660 align:middle line:84%
We've asked science
to tell us who we are.

00:23:01.660 --> 00:23:03.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And they don't tell us.

00:23:03.080 --> 00:23:05.550 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: Well,
science, pure science,

00:23:05.550 --> 00:23:07.590 align:middle line:84%
is now revealing
the information.

00:23:07.590 --> 00:23:11.440 align:middle line:84%
It's not being accepted
in the mainstream.

00:23:11.440 --> 00:23:12.950 align:middle line:84%
So the textbooks
in the classrooms

00:23:12.950 --> 00:23:15.229 align:middle line:84%
are not accepting what
the science is telling us.

00:23:15.229 --> 00:23:16.520 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is it telling us?

00:23:16.520 --> 00:23:18.300 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: For
example, evolution--

00:23:18.300 --> 00:23:20.180 align:middle line:84%
we'll just take
evolution because that's

00:23:20.180 --> 00:23:22.670 align:middle line:84%
on a lot of people's
minds right now.

00:23:22.670 --> 00:23:24.780 align:middle line:84%
In the public
classroom, a teacher

00:23:24.780 --> 00:23:26.420 align:middle line:84%
can only teach the
curricula that's

00:23:26.420 --> 00:23:27.950 align:middle line:90%
been approved by a school board.

00:23:27.950 --> 00:23:28.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:23:28.590 --> 00:23:28.670 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: All right.

00:23:28.670 --> 00:23:29.320 align:middle line:90%
The school board--

00:23:29.320 --> 00:23:30.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You can't
deviate from that.

00:23:30.080 --> 00:23:32.490 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: If the school
board does not accept--

00:23:32.490 --> 00:23:34.360 align:middle line:84%
even though it's peer
reviewed science--

00:23:34.360 --> 00:23:36.370 align:middle line:84%
if the school board
does not accept that,

00:23:36.370 --> 00:23:37.310 align:middle line:90%
it cannot be taught.

00:23:37.310 --> 00:23:37.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or that
teacher gets fired.

00:23:37.590 --> 00:23:39.970 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: So we're
teaching our young people--

00:23:39.970 --> 00:23:41.640 align:middle line:90%
or the teacher gets fired, yeah.

00:23:41.640 --> 00:23:44.580 align:middle line:84%
We're teaching our
young people the story

00:23:44.580 --> 00:23:47.340 align:middle line:84%
of separation that has led
to so many of the crises

00:23:47.340 --> 00:23:48.090 align:middle line:90%
that we're seeing.

00:23:48.090 --> 00:23:49.495 align:middle line:84%
It makes us feel
separate from ourselves.

00:23:49.495 --> 00:23:50.078 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:23:50.078 --> 00:23:51.310 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: From one another.

00:23:51.310 --> 00:23:53.540 align:middle line:84%
And I've asked professors
and friends of mine.

00:23:53.540 --> 00:23:57.030 align:middle line:84%
I said, why can't you share
this in the classroom?

00:23:57.030 --> 00:24:00.304 align:middle line:84%
Why can't you
share this science?

00:24:00.304 --> 00:24:02.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they're petrified
to share this, aren't they?

00:24:02.720 --> 00:24:05.947 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: There are four--
money, ego, power, and habit.

00:24:05.947 --> 00:24:06.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:24:06.530 --> 00:24:08.988 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And one of those,
one of the professors, he said,

00:24:08.988 --> 00:24:11.670 align:middle line:84%
do you know-- he's a male--
he said, do you know what that

00:24:11.670 --> 00:24:16.152 align:middle line:84%
would mean to my 40-year career
if I had to stand in front

00:24:16.152 --> 00:24:17.610 align:middle line:84%
of a classroom say,
everything I've

00:24:17.610 --> 00:24:20.750 align:middle line:84%
taught until this point
is no longer true?

00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:23.040 align:middle line:84%
So to him, it would
say he was a failure.

00:24:23.040 --> 00:24:24.940 align:middle line:84%
What I said to him,
I said, it would

00:24:24.940 --> 00:24:27.610 align:middle line:84%
be a beautiful demonstration
of the power of science

00:24:27.610 --> 00:24:31.720 align:middle line:84%
and your ability to
constantly update what science

00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:32.970 align:middle line:90%
is telling us about our world.

00:24:32.970 --> 00:24:34.803 align:middle line:84%
He said, do you know
how much money it would

00:24:34.803 --> 00:24:36.057 align:middle line:90%
cost to change the textbooks?

00:24:36.057 --> 00:24:38.140 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, you know,
look how much money we

00:24:38.140 --> 00:24:40.740 align:middle line:90%
spend a war, so why not?

00:24:40.740 --> 00:24:41.700 align:middle line:90%
Habit.

00:24:41.700 --> 00:24:45.390 align:middle line:84%
He said, you know, it is
a habit to teach this.

00:24:45.390 --> 00:24:46.600 align:middle line:90%
Now it is changing.

00:24:46.600 --> 00:24:48.850 align:middle line:84%
And it's changing
slowly, George.

00:24:48.850 --> 00:24:50.260 align:middle line:90%
And this is only one place.

00:24:50.260 --> 00:24:51.760 align:middle line:90%
Evolution is only one place.

00:24:51.760 --> 00:24:54.270 align:middle line:84%
But it's the place that's
directly relevant to the God

00:24:54.270 --> 00:24:54.770 align:middle line:90%
code.

00:24:54.770 --> 00:24:56.603 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But will we
get that answer, Gregg?

00:24:56.603 --> 00:24:58.780 align:middle line:90%
Why are we here?

00:24:58.780 --> 00:25:03.960 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I think we
will find the evidence

00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:05.640 align:middle line:90%
of the circumstances.

00:25:05.640 --> 00:25:09.380 align:middle line:84%
The actual reason, I
think, is something

00:25:09.380 --> 00:25:11.510 align:middle line:84%
that we have to
find for ourselves.

00:25:11.510 --> 00:25:12.304 align:middle line:90%
I think we're--

00:25:12.304 --> 00:25:13.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Individually?

00:25:13.220 --> 00:25:14.178 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Individually.

00:25:14.178 --> 00:25:15.990 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what
we're going find.

00:25:15.990 --> 00:25:17.632 align:middle line:84%
A good friend of
mine was watching

00:25:17.632 --> 00:25:18.590 align:middle line:90%
the movie "The Matrix."

00:25:18.590 --> 00:25:19.550 align:middle line:84%
I know a lot of our
viewers have seen it.

00:25:19.550 --> 00:25:19.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Great movie.

00:25:19.990 --> 00:25:20.850 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:25:20.850 --> 00:25:22.970 align:middle line:84%
I've cited that on
the radio show a lot.

00:25:22.970 --> 00:25:24.360 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: I love it as well.

00:25:24.360 --> 00:25:25.874 align:middle line:90%
It's one that I have by the TV.

00:25:25.874 --> 00:25:28.040 align:middle line:84%
And when I'm writing into
the wee hours the morning,

00:25:28.040 --> 00:25:29.307 align:middle line:90%
there's two movies.

00:25:29.307 --> 00:25:31.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't watch them all the
way through, but I'll--

00:25:31.390 --> 00:25:32.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: "Contact" and "Matrix."

00:25:32.540 --> 00:25:32.930 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: You know.

00:25:32.930 --> 00:25:33.770 align:middle line:90%
How'd you know that?

00:25:33.770 --> 00:25:35.755 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because it's
the same with me.

00:25:35.755 --> 00:25:37.260 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And I don't watch
them all the way through.

00:25:37.260 --> 00:25:39.450 align:middle line:84%
But I like the part where
they solve the codes because I

00:25:39.450 --> 00:25:40.560 align:middle line:90%
think there's a lot to that.

00:25:40.560 --> 00:25:42.500 align:middle line:84%
And you know, where does
that come from anyway?

00:25:42.500 --> 00:25:44.583 align:middle line:84%
So my friend said, you
think it's science fiction.

00:25:44.583 --> 00:25:47.527 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Matrix" is actually
a documentary about us--

00:25:47.527 --> 00:25:48.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:25:48.110 --> 00:25:50.151 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: --and the way
things work in the world.

00:25:50.151 --> 00:25:53.570 align:middle line:84%
So it may be that by working
backward through the code,

00:25:53.570 --> 00:25:56.250 align:middle line:84%
we do arrive at the doorstep
of an architect at some point.

00:25:56.250 --> 00:26:01.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you could get
an answer to one question,

00:26:01.110 --> 00:26:03.262 align:middle line:90%
what would that question be?

00:26:03.262 --> 00:26:04.720 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I think
it's the question

00:26:04.720 --> 00:26:06.170 align:middle line:90%
we're asking right now.

00:26:06.170 --> 00:26:07.250 align:middle line:90%
Why us?

00:26:07.250 --> 00:26:07.810 align:middle line:90%
Why here?

00:26:07.810 --> 00:26:08.350 align:middle line:90%
Why now?

00:26:08.350 --> 00:26:11.630 align:middle line:90%


